KamAZ, Magnitogorsk, Norilsk, Synergy: Russian Equity Preview

-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 
2011-04-06T20:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/kamaz-magnitogorsk-norilsk-synergy-russian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close of trading in Moscow.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  climbed 0.6 percent to 1,859.99,
the highest since June 2008. The dollar-denominated RTS Index
gained 1.1 percent to 2,110.90.  OAO  KamAZ (KMAZ)  :  Russia ’s largest truckmaker, part-
owned by Daimler AG, may boost revenue 25 percent this year to
93 billion rubles ($3.3 billion) and break even after losses in
2010, Interfax reported. KamAZ rose 0.6 percent to 75.30 rubles.  OAO Magnitogorsk Iron & Steel (MAGN RX): Russian
billionaire Victor Rashnikov’s steelmaker is scheduled to report
its fourth-quarter financial results. Magnitogorsk advanced 0.3
percent to 31.63 rubles.  OAO Norilsk Nickel (GMKN RX): Copper futures rose the most
in two weeks as Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc. said that
demand in  China  will continue to increase. Norilsk, Russia’s
largest producer of nickel and copper, rose 0.1 percent to 7,757
rubles.  OAO Synergy (SYNG RX): A Russian vodka maker may report its
financial results for 2010. Synergy advanced 2 percent to
1,214.80 rubles.  To contact the reporters on this story: Ilya Khrennikov in
Moscow at   ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amanda Jordan at 
 ajordan11@bloomberg.net . 